<p><i><b>The Anatomy of Melancholy</b></i> (Full title <i>The Anatomy of Melancholy, What it is: With all the Kinds, Causes, Symptomes, Prognostickes, and Several Cures of it. In Three Maine Partitions with their several Sections, Members, and Subsections. Philosophically, Historically, Opened and Cut up.</i>) is a book by <a href="/wiki/Robert_Burton_(scholar)" title="Robert Burton (scholar)">Robert Burton</a>, first published in 1621.</p>
